      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, you said social spending is \"far more critical\"... but isn't it true that high debt eventually causes interest rates to spike and crashes the whole economy? doesn't that end up hurting the poor way more than a lack of social programs would? wouldn't you say focusing on the debt is the only truly responsible way to protect everyone?",
