      "content": "While high debt can cause interest rate spikes, the long-term cost of a broken social safety net is far greater because it destroys the very workforce and consumer base needed to generate the tax revenue required to pay down that debt. A government that ignores healthcare and housing creates a cycle of poverty and stagnation that no amount of debt reduction can fix, whereas investing in these areas builds a resilient economy capable of sustaining itself. Therefore, the only truly responsible path is to prioritize social infrastructure to ensure economic growth, which naturally leads to a sustainable reduction in national debt over time.",
