      "content": "i hear what you're saying, but it feels like you're almost dismissing the whole idea of fiscal discipline as if it's just an afterthought. if someone argues that you can't build an economy if the currency is devalued or the government is insolvent, are they just wrong? or is there a way to see fiscal restraint as a moral necessity rather than just an obstacle to social spending?",
